# Model config: Qwen3-Coder-Next with static YaRN for ~1M context -- model-intrinsic.
#
# Same UD-Q5_K_M weights as models/qwen3-coder-next.env, plus rope scaling.
# Native context is 262,144 (config.json: max_position_embeddings, rope_scaling
# null). The Qwen3-Next-80B-A3B card documents the official extension recipe:
#   rope_scaling = {rope_type: yarn, factor: 4.0,
#                   original_max_position_embeddings: 262144}   -> ~1,048,576
# mapped here to llama.cpp flags (--rope-scaling yarn --rope-scale 4
# --yarn-orig-ctx 262144). NOTE: that recipe is published for the sibling
# Qwen3-Next model (identical architecture/native length); Qwen has not
# restated it for Coder-Next specifically.
#
# WHY A SEPARATE CONFIG: static YaRN is applied to ALL requests and Qwen warns
# it "potentially impact[s] performance on shorter texts". Keep the unscaled
# qwen3-coder-next config for day-to-day coding; launch this one only when you
# actually need >256K. If your long jobs top out lower (e.g. 512K), shrink
# --rope-scale to ceil(needed/262144) for less short-context damage.
#
# Sampling: identical to models/qwen3-coder-next.env (Qwen card + Unsloth).

: "${MODEL:=Qwen3-Coder-Next/UD-Q5_K_M/Qwen3-Coder-Next-UD-Q5_K_M-00001-of-00003.gguf}"

LLAMA_ARGS+=(--temp 1.0 --top-p 0.95 --top-k 40 --min-p 0.01 --repeat-penalty 1.0)
LLAMA_ARGS+=(--rope-scaling yarn --rope-scale 4 --yarn-orig-ctx 262144)
LLAMA_ARGS+=(--alias qwen3-coder-next-1m)
